Fujimori came to the hospital for medical checks
The former President Alberto Fujimori was taken on Tuesday in a public hospital in order to investigate the muscle loss of his legs, informed his family doctor.
The 72-year-old Fujimori to 25 years in prison for violation of human rights during his time in government (1990 - 2000), has several diseases, including cancer of the tongue, which operates four times and under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, Congress member and his personal doctor, said the television that would investigate Fujimori for three days in the hospital Peruvian Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas reason for his pain and loss of muscle in the lower body links.
Aguinaga commented that could be pardoned his opinion, Fujimori for humanitarian reasons, but he does not do it, because he is innocent.
He was operated on four times for cancer of the tongue, and he has lost 18 kg weight. Other diseases, such as a heavy erosive Gastritis, a Zyste in the pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and Durchblutungsprobleme in the legs, the doctor.
Fujimori has since September 2007 in the penitentiary Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the murder of 25 people by the Peruvian army death squad during his time in government was condemned.
